                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.55/25.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-09-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 24, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My appointment in charge of Chinese interests in Panama favorably received by
                    Government and press. The Minister for Foreign Affairs has announced
                    postponement of the application of Law 50 giving time for its full
                    consideration. Fourteen hundred Chinese cédulas today deposited with the
                    Legation for examination and safekeeping. Kindly forward assurance of my
                    appreciation and earnest efforts to the Chinese Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wicker.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
